{{Politics of Tajikistan}}
A '''constitutional referendum''' was held in [[Tajikistan]] on 26 September 1999.<ref>[[Dieter Nohlen]], Florian Grotz & Christof Hartmann (2001) ''Elections in Asia: A data handbook, Volume I'', p462 {{ISBN|0-19-924958-X}}</ref> The changes included legalising religious political parties, introducing a [[bicameralism|bicameral]] parliament, and lengthening the president's term from five to seven years. They were approved by 75.3% of voters, with a turnout of 91.5%.<ref>Nohlen et al., p464</ref>
